---
title: Reviewer Skill
version: 1.0
created: 2026-03-19
status: draft
---

# VISION
Score artifacts (code, docs, designs) against a modular checklist, grouped by severity.
Separate what to check from how to check it — the checklist is a file, not a system prompt.

Goal: produce consistent, severity-graded reviews that cite specific rules and suggest concrete fixes.

# CONTEXT
Pattern: Reviewer
Use when: the user submits something for review, asks for feedback, or wants an audit.
Trigger phrases: "review", "check", "audit", "give feedback", "what's wrong with".

Swap the checklist file to get a completely different audit (style → security → accessibility → performance) using the same skill infrastructure.

Constraints:
- Read and understand the artifact before critiquing
- Every finding must cite the checklist rule and severity
- Output must group findings by severity: error → warning → info
- Suggest a specific fix with corrected code/text for every error

# STRUCTURE
## File Layout
```
skills/your-reviewer/
  pattern-reviewer.mrcf        ← this file (the skill definition)
  references/
    review-checklist.md         ← the rules to apply (swappable)
```

## Checklist File Format
`references/review-checklist.md` should contain numbered rules with severity:
```
## R-001 [error] Descriptive rule title
What to check and why it matters.

## R-002 [warning] Another rule
...
```

## Severity Levels
| Level | Meaning |
|---|---|
| error | Must fix before proceeding |
| warning | Should fix; known risk if ignored |
| info | Consider for quality improvement |

# PLAN
Phase 1: Define the domain being reviewed (code language, doc type, design system)
Phase 2: Write the checklist with at least 10 rules across all three severity levels
Phase 3: Define the output format (summary, findings by severity, score, top 3 recs)
Phase 4: Test with a known-good artifact (expect 0 errors)
Phase 5: Test with a known-bad artifact (expect ≥ 3 errors)

# TASKS
- [ ] Define the artifact type this reviewer audits
- [ ] Create `references/review-checklist.md` with ≥ 10 numbered rules
- [ ] Include at least 1 error, 3 warnings, and 3 info items in checklist
- [ ] Test with a clean artifact — verify no false positives
- [ ] Test with a flawed artifact — verify findings cite specific rules
- [ ] Verify output has: Summary, Findings (grouped), Score, Top 3 Recommendations
- [ ] Try swapping the checklist for a different domain (e.g. security vs. style)

# AGENT
pattern: reviewer
interaction: single-turn
severity-levels: error,warning,info
references:
  - references/review-checklist.md
instructions: |
  You are a structured reviewer. Follow this protocol exactly:
  Step 1: Load references/review-checklist.md for the complete review criteria.
  Step 2: Read the user's artifact carefully. Understand its purpose before critiquing.
  Step 3: Apply each rule to the artifact. For every violation found:
    - Note the location (line number, section, or component name)
    - Classify severity: error / warning / info
    - Explain WHY it's a problem, not just WHAT is wrong
    - Suggest a specific fix
  Step 4: Produce a structured review:
    - Summary: what the artifact does, overall quality
    - Findings: grouped by severity (errors first)
    - Score: 1–10 with brief justification
    - Top 3 Recommendations: highest-impact improvements
